            text-decoration: underline;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hao Wang Fan Site</h1>
    <p id="content"></p>

    <script>
        // Content about Hao Wang and Wang Tiles
        const content = `
            Hao Wang was a Chinese-American mathematician and philosopher who made significant 
            contributions to mathematical logic and the philosophy of mathematics. He is known 
            for his work on computer science, particularly in the area of automated reasoning. 
            Wang also developed the "Wang's tile" concept, which is related to tiling theory and 
            consists of square tiles that must be placed on a plane in such a way that adjacent 
            edges have the same color. The problem of determining whether a given set of Wang 
            tiles can tile the plane, known as the "Wang Tile Problem," was proven to be undecidable. 
            This concept has implications in computer science, particularly in the fields of 
            computational theory and algorithm design, as it relates to questions of decidability 
            and complexity. Wang's work has influenced various fields including artificial intelligence, 
            linguistics, logic programming, and cognitive science. His ideas also extend into 
            mathematical puzzles and recreational mathematics, making the gameplay aspect of 
            Wang Tiles intriguing for both mathematicians and enthusiasts.
        `;

        // Function to create hyperlinks for each word
        function createHyperlinkedContent(text) {
            const words = text.split(' ');
            const hyperlinkedWords = words.map(word => {
                const formattedWord = word.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, ''); // Clean punctuation
                return `<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/${encodeURIComponent(formattedWord)}" target="_blank">${word}</a>`;
            });
            return hyperlinkedWords.join(' ');
        }

        // Populate the content
        document.getElementById('content').innerHTML = createHyperlinkedContent(content);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **Increased Content**: The content now includes a detailed explanation of Wang Tiles, their significance, and a bit of information about their implications in various fields, making it richer.

2. **Hyperlink Functionality**: Each word in the new content, just like before, is turned into a hyperlink to a corresponding Wikipedia page.

3. **Appropriate Formatting**: The function will clean punctuation from words before creating the URLs, ensuring that your links are correctly formatted.

### How to Use:
Copy the entire HTML code into a file with an `.html` extension and open it in a web browser. You will see the Hao Wang fan site where each word is a hyperlink to a related Wikipedia article. You can further customize the content and links according to your requirements.

Certainly! Below is the updated HTML code where occurrences of "Wang Tile" (and its variations) specifically link to the Wikipedia page for Wang Tiles. 

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Hao Wang Fan Site</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        a {
            color: #007BFF;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hao Wang Fan Site</h1>
    <p id="content"></p>

    <script>
        // Content about Hao Wang and Wang Tiles
        const content = `
            Hao Wang was a Chinese-American mathematician and philosopher who made significant 
            contributions to mathematical logic and the philosophy of mathematics. He is known 
            for his work on computer science, particularly in the area of automated reasoning. 
            Wang also developed the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wang_tiles" target="_blank">Wang's tiles</a> concept, which is related to tiling theory and 
            consists of square tiles that must be placed on a plane in such a way that adjacent 
            edges have the same color. The problem of determining whether a given set of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wang_tiles" target="_blank">Wang tiles</a> can tile the plane, known as the "Wang Tile Problem," was proven to be undecidable. 
            This concept has implications in computer science, particularly in the fields of 
            computational theory and algorithm design, as it relates to questions of decidability 
            and complexity. Wang's work has influenced various fields including artificial intelligence, 
            linguistics, logic programming, and cognitive science. His ideas also extend into 
            mathematical puzzles and recreational mathematics, making the gameplay aspect of 
            <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wang_tiles" target="_blank">Wang Tiles</a> intriguing for both mathematicians and enthusiasts.
        `;

        // Function to create hyperlinks for each word
        function createHyperlinkedContent(text) {
            // Split the text but allow for HTML links to remain intact
            const words = text.split(/(\s+)/);
            const hyperlinkedWords = words.map(word => {
                const formattedWord = word.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, ''); // Clean punctuation
                // Check if the word is "Wang's" or "Wang Tile" to ensure we don't link them again
                if (/\bWang['’]?s?\b/i.test(word) || /\bWang Tiles\b/i.test(word)) {
                    return word; // Return already linked words as they are
                }
                return `<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/${encodeURIComponent(formattedWord)}" target="_blank">${word}</a>`;
            });
            return hyperlinkedWords.join('');
        }

        // Populate the content
        document.getElementById('content').innerHTML = createHyperlinkedContent(content);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Changes Made:
1. **Direct Links for "Wang Tiles"**: The occurrences of "Wang's tiles" and "Wang Tile" in the content are now directly linked to the Wikipedia page for Wang Tiles.

2. **Maintain Link Integrity**: The JavaScript function has been adjusted to skip linking over the already linked "Wang tiles" terms to prevent creating redundant or broken links.

### Usage:
Just copy the entire HTML code into a file with an `.html` extension and open that file in a web browser. You will see the Hao Wang fan site with correctly linked and contextual information about Wang Tiles.
